summary:
In the trailer for Avengers: Endgame, we see Nebula’s hand on what looks like someone’s chest, in a sort of act of grief. 
At...
body:
Guys. I noticed something.

In the trailer for Avengers: Endgame, we see Nebula’s hand on what looks like someone’s chest, in a sort of act of grief.

At first I thought it was Tony in space and he had died due to starvation or oxygen loss or something like that. But now we know that isn’t true. I was thinking. What if it is Nebula’s hand. And it is Tony’s chest. And she is mourning him. But it’s after the fight. We’ve won, Thanos is dead, but so put some of our heroes. Including Tony. And Nebula mourns him and Marvel decided to show us. It would make sense. They just fought on Earth in a park or something or at Thanos’ farm place near trees.

But also in the corner it looks like some kind of metal machine (which we know Tony works with) which could be debris from the thing Tony and Nebula were building in one of the trailers.

And I know that Tony has the housing unit for the nano-particles in his chest, but what if something happens to that or he has to take it out for a new suit or machine he makes.

I don’t see any nano-particles but I dunno it could be a shadow.

“Right, exactly,” Evans says. I saw, like, the first hour of it.“ "After I die by Tony’s hand, I just said, You know what? I can’t watch this.”
